  "text": "In joint prediction models for Chinese, lattice structures are not typically used. Commonly these models are formulated in a transition-based framework at the character level [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . While this formulation can handle a large space of possible word segmentations, it can only capture features that are instantiated based on the stack and queue status. Our approach offers two advantages over prior work:",
